[Student "S"]
{[show S]
[BID 1NT] [BID 2!S] [BID Pass]
[show NS]
NORTH, with 11 points and six \Ss, knows immediately that the final contract will be 4\S 
since the partners must have at least eight \Ss and at least 26 points.
 

 
She concludes that it might be better for SOUTH to be the Declarer so she bids 2\H 
as a Jacoby Transfer. When SOUTH makes the required 2\S bid she just bids 4\S which 
closes the auction with SOUTH as Declarer.}


