Just having a 4-card Major doesn't mean you must automatically use Stayman.
 

 
Here SOUTH has a 4-card \S suit, but decides not to seek a 4-4 fit because his 
hand wouldn't have any ruffing values in a \S contract. He bids 3NT.
 

 
Notice that even though NORTH also has four \Ss the 4-4 fit is not useful to them in 
a \S contract because neither hand can ruff any losers.}


